# Repository Baseline

Keep this baseline short and broadly useful. Let ownership nodes carry path-specific guidance and use overlays only for real cross-cutting concerns.

If the repository needs a consistent closure stance, state it briefly here. A short hybrid default is often enough: reconcile small and certain downstream follow-through in the current pass, and carry broader or less certain work forward explicitly.

Use skills for reusable workflows that would bloat always-on instructions, keep them outcome-based rather than one per trigger, and prefer scripts, CI checks, or runbooks for exact repeatable procedures.
